17/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) arrested four Bosniaks on Wednesday (September 16th), suspected of committing war crimes against Croat civilians in 1993 in the village of Trusina. 
The four were alleged members of Bosnian Muslim units that attacked the village on April 16th 1993, killing 19 civilians and three Croat soldiers. 
SIPA members searched 17 locations in different parts of the country to find evidence related to this case, including the Sarajevo apartment of Bosnian Muslim wartime Army Chief of Staff Sefer Halilovic. 
(Dnevni Avaz, BHRT, RTRS, Tanjug - 16/09/09)
